WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:03.003
Tiffany:
Previously, on "Chucky"...

00:03.481 --> 00:04.221
- Move.

00:05.048 --> 00:05.657
- Now, there's a lot going on,

00:06.267 --> 00:07.572
so pay attention.

00:08.965 --> 00:09.748
Jake's doll chucky was alive,
and he killed his dad,

00:11.098 --> 00:12.012
and he killed Oliver,
and the cop at the hospital,

00:13.491 --> 00:14.188
Junior's housekeeper, too,
and he wouldn't stop killing.

00:15.189 --> 00:17.626
[screaming]
- I like to be hugged.

00:17.669 --> 00:20.455
- Making up stupid shit
like that is just embarrassing.

00:20.498 --> 00:23.327
- Meanwhile, the mayor
went all Megyn Kelly,

00:23.371 --> 00:25.199
until the principal
lost her head.

00:25.242 --> 00:26.809
[screaming]

00:26.852 --> 00:28.854
- We killed him!

00:28.898 --> 00:29.812
- Hello?
- Yeah, I'm calling

00:29.855 --> 00:31.292
about the doll.

00:31.335 --> 00:32.815
Have you checked
his batteries?

00:34.599 --> 00:36.427
- My name is Nica Pierce.

00:36.471 --> 00:38.342
Chucky murdered
my whole family.

00:38.386 --> 00:39.865
He split his soul into pieces.

00:39.909 --> 00:42.216
One of those pieces
is inside me.

00:42.259 --> 00:43.478
- Who's Chucky?

00:43.521 --> 00:45.219
- What are you doing
on the floor?

00:45.262 --> 00:46.655
- Uhh--

00:46.698 --> 00:48.309
- Have you thought about
telling Junior first?

00:48.352 --> 00:49.658
- As if Logan
doesn't put enough

00:49.701 --> 00:51.225
pressure on Junior as it is.

00:51.268 --> 00:53.096
- Re: your illness?

00:53.140 --> 00:57.796
- Ade due Damballa.

00:57.840 --> 01:01.583
Give me the power,
I beg of you.

01:01.626 --> 01:04.412
I'm Tommy. Wanna play?

01:04.455 --> 01:06.718
- Best if we keep this Nica
bullshit between us, huh?

01:06.762 --> 01:09.330
- Ooh, did I mention

01:09.373 --> 01:12.289
I took over the life
of my favorite celebrity?

01:12.333 --> 01:15.553
I wanna be Jennifer Tilly.

01:15.597 --> 01:17.207
I wanna be a star.

01:17.251 --> 01:21.211
- Ade due Damballa. And switch.

01:21.255 --> 01:22.908
And switch.

01:22.952 --> 01:24.388
Switch, switch, switch.

01:24.432 --> 01:25.824
[exhales]

01:25.868 --> 01:28.479
Anyhow, lots to get to.

01:28.523 --> 01:31.221
Television is so exciting.

01:32.570 --> 01:35.530
[upbeat music]

01:35.573 --> 01:42.450
♪

02:14.308 --> 02:15.744
[doorbell dings]

02:17.876 --> 02:19.269
- Can I help you?

02:19.313 --> 02:20.488
- Is this the
Morrison residence?

02:20.531 --> 02:22.229
- Yes.
- Hi.

02:22.272 --> 02:23.969
We're from the U.S. Census.

02:24.013 --> 02:25.623
Can we have a few minutes
of your time?

02:25.667 --> 02:27.408
- Well, we were just about
to sit down to eat.

02:27.451 --> 02:28.887
- Oh, this won't take long.

02:28.931 --> 02:31.455
We just want to make sure
everyone is counted.

02:31.499 --> 02:33.849
It's important
to be represented.

02:33.892 --> 02:35.329
- All right, come on in.

02:38.245 --> 02:40.421
- So, the Census is pretty
straightforward these days.

02:40.464 --> 02:41.900
We're just gonna ask you
a few questions

02:41.944 --> 02:43.293
and we'll get out of your hair.

02:43.337 --> 02:44.599
- Happy to do our part.

02:44.642 --> 02:46.209
- So, how many members
in the household?

02:46.253 --> 02:48.472
- Just the three of us?
- Ages?

02:48.516 --> 02:51.823
- 39.
- 38, and Becky here

02:51.867 --> 02:53.651
just turned seven,
didn't you, Becks?

02:53.695 --> 02:55.305
- I'm a grownup.

02:55.349 --> 02:57.829
- I bet you are.
I bet you're really smart too.

02:57.873 --> 02:59.440
- Any recent property damage?

03:03.052 --> 03:04.923
- No, not that I can think of.

03:04.967 --> 03:06.664
- We should move on
to the occupations.

03:06.708 --> 03:09.972
- Any fires or major injuries?

03:10.015 --> 03:11.452
Freak accidents?

03:13.280 --> 03:16.239
- God, no. Nothing like that.

03:16.283 --> 03:17.980
- We have to ask.

03:18.023 --> 03:20.504
Um, so, you were saying?
Your occupation?

03:20.548 --> 03:23.464
- Any new dolls in the house?

03:23.507 --> 03:24.900
- Dolls?

03:24.943 --> 03:28.295
- What kind of census
are you taking exactly?

03:28.338 --> 03:30.427
- It's a new thing we're doing
at the Bureau.

03:30.471 --> 03:31.689
You know, we ask
a few questions

03:31.733 --> 03:33.996
to get the kids excited
about the Census.

03:35.737 --> 03:37.565
- That's wonderful.

03:37.608 --> 03:38.740
- Becky, why don't you go get

03:38.783 --> 03:39.958
some of your friends
from your room?

03:44.354 --> 03:46.661
- Uh, it's so important
to start them early.

03:46.704 --> 03:48.010
- Mm.

03:48.053 --> 03:51.013
[eerie music]

03:51.056 --> 03:54.799
♪

03:54.843 --> 03:58.803
- Here's Binty and
Mrs. Fluff and Jojo and--

03:58.847 --> 04:01.545
- Sweetheart, are these
all your friends?

04:01.589 --> 04:03.982
'Cause it's really important
that we count everyone.

04:04.026 --> 04:05.723
- This is everybody.

04:05.767 --> 04:08.770
Mrs. Fluff and Jojo
and Monkey Beans

04:08.813 --> 04:12.382
and wait, I forgot Charlie.

04:12.426 --> 04:13.905
- Oh.
- Well, go get him. Go get him.

04:13.949 --> 04:15.733
[both laugh]

04:15.777 --> 04:17.082
- That is her favorite.

04:17.126 --> 04:24.046
♪

04:33.621 --> 04:37.059
- Hi. I'm...Charlie.

04:37.102 --> 04:38.713
Wanna play?

04:39.931 --> 04:46.851
♪

04:48.984 --> 04:51.726
- You made me do this.

04:51.769 --> 04:52.944
- Do what?

04:54.032 --> 04:56.774
- [gasps] Ah!

04:56.818 --> 04:58.602
- Ah!
- [girl screams]

04:58.646 --> 04:59.951
- Oh! Oh!

04:59.995 --> 05:02.737
Oh, oh, oh, oh!
- [screaming]

05:02.780 --> 05:04.869
- Fuck you, Andy!

05:04.913 --> 05:11.789
♪

05:15.663 --> 05:17.099
- Thank you
for your cooperation.

05:17.142 --> 05:19.928
♪

05:19.971 --> 05:22.887
[tires screeching]

05:22.931 --> 05:29.851
♪

05:31.461 --> 05:34.421
[playful spooky music]

05:34.464 --> 05:41.341
♪

05:59.620 --> 06:00.838
- Ohh.

06:03.537 --> 06:06.061
Those people today,
what if they talk?

06:07.758 --> 06:10.108
- You and I both know
nobody's gonna believe 'em.

06:11.458 --> 06:14.939
- That little girl,
she's gonna be traumatized.

06:14.983 --> 06:17.159
She's never gonna be the same.

06:17.202 --> 06:19.030
- She'll be alive.

06:19.074 --> 06:20.858
Besides, you and me
went through a lot as kids.

06:20.902 --> 06:22.077
- Come on!

06:22.120 --> 06:23.731
[thrilling music]

06:23.774 --> 06:26.516
[gasps]
- Uh!

06:26.560 --> 06:28.431
We turned out okay.

06:32.087 --> 06:33.654
You did, at least.

06:33.697 --> 06:36.178
- Reminds me,
why didn't you tell me

06:36.221 --> 06:38.963
you were keeping a living
Chucky head locked in a safe?

06:40.791 --> 06:42.053
- Yeah.

06:43.533 --> 06:45.883
Thanks for taking care of that.

06:45.927 --> 06:48.233
- You didn't answer
my question.

06:48.277 --> 06:52.194
Why did you keep him alive
for four years?

06:52.237 --> 06:54.501
- What difference does it make?

06:54.544 --> 06:55.458
- I don't know.
Doesn't sound like

06:55.502 --> 06:57.504
very rational behavior.

06:57.547 --> 07:01.508
- There's nothing rational
about any of this!

07:01.551 --> 07:03.118
It's something I picked up
in military school.

07:04.511 --> 07:05.729
Get to know your enemy.

07:05.773 --> 07:09.690
You can learn a lot from a POW,

07:09.733 --> 07:10.952
if you persuade him
hard enough.

07:12.519 --> 07:14.999
- What did you learn?

07:15.043 --> 07:17.001
- He scream
the loudest at fire.

07:17.045 --> 07:19.221
- [screaming]

07:19.264 --> 07:20.744
Those screams were my favorite.

07:22.616 --> 07:25.096
Even louder than my own.

07:25.140 --> 07:27.142
- Okay, so there's just
one left, right?

07:27.185 --> 07:28.926
- Yeah.

07:28.970 --> 07:30.711
One doll left.

07:32.974 --> 07:34.889
- Okay, what aren't you
telling me?

07:38.545 --> 07:41.939
- Well, Chucky broke his soul
into pieces,

07:41.983 --> 07:45.508
but the last piece,
it didn't go into a doll.

07:47.684 --> 07:49.686
- Where did it go?

07:49.730 --> 07:52.080
- Let's just say that murder
isn't the worst thing

07:52.123 --> 07:53.821
Chucky can do to you.

08:03.221 --> 08:05.615
- The female wildebeests

08:05.659 --> 08:08.052
begin to give birth
to their offspring.

08:08.096 --> 08:09.663
all: Eww!

08:09.706 --> 08:12.535
- The calves fall
to the ground

08:12.579 --> 08:15.320
along with the afterbirth.

08:15.364 --> 08:18.628
- Okay, let's simmer
down, guys.

08:18.672 --> 08:22.110
- Others take a bit more time.
[knock on door]

08:22.153 --> 08:24.678
- Rachel Fairchild,
you're under arrest

08:24.721 --> 08:26.984
for the murders
of Megan McVey, Oliver Hayden,

08:27.028 --> 08:30.118
and Detective Sean Peyton.
- What?

08:30.161 --> 08:32.642
What? Are you joking?

08:32.686 --> 08:35.123
- Mom.

08:35.166 --> 08:36.907
She didn't do it.
- Lower your voice.

08:36.951 --> 08:37.995
How do you know
she didn't do it?

08:40.781 --> 08:43.131
- I just do.

08:43.174 --> 08:44.872
- I'll see you at home.

08:49.703 --> 08:51.226
- No, stop! Please!

08:51.269 --> 08:53.924
Devon's right.
We know she didn't do it.

08:53.968 --> 08:55.230
- All right, let's go.

09:02.411 --> 09:04.065
- Go ahead and get back
in the classroom.

09:09.244 --> 09:10.767
- We should have told 'em
about Chucky.

09:10.811 --> 09:12.639
- Yeah, brilliant.
Because I've always wanted

09:12.682 --> 09:13.770
to be institutionalized.

09:13.814 --> 09:15.119
How about you?

09:15.163 --> 09:17.208
- Lexy's right.
We can't just tell anyone.

09:17.252 --> 09:18.862
We have to find him
and kill him.

09:18.906 --> 09:20.821
- But we did kill him.
I mean, we were all there.

09:20.864 --> 09:22.170
- We all saw what happened
to McVey.

09:22.213 --> 09:23.998
He's still out there.

09:27.044 --> 09:29.133
- Shit.

09:29.177 --> 09:30.700
It's gotta be Tommy.

09:30.744 --> 09:32.006
- What, your sister's doll?

09:32.049 --> 09:33.398
I thought you said
you checked him out.

09:33.442 --> 09:35.226
- I did. Now he's missing.

09:35.270 --> 09:36.706
- What? Since when?

09:36.750 --> 09:37.968
- Well, how's that
even possible?

09:38.012 --> 09:40.014
- This is serious.
We have to find him.

09:44.018 --> 09:46.673
- I have an idea.

09:46.716 --> 09:48.239
Andy Barclay.

09:48.283 --> 09:50.067
- Who's Andy Barclay?

09:50.111 --> 09:52.330
- He was this kid in the '80s
whose babysitter was murdered.

09:52.374 --> 09:54.158
He always said Chucky did it.

09:54.202 --> 09:56.683
The whole Charles Lee Ray
connection, everything,

09:56.726 --> 09:58.772
it all comes back
to Andy Barclay.

09:58.815 --> 10:00.774
- Well, you think he'll know
how to find Chucky?

10:00.817 --> 10:02.732
- Maybe.

10:02.776 --> 10:04.778
- Let's do it.
Let's talk to him.

10:04.821 --> 10:06.301
- My house, after school.
Come as soon as you can.

10:09.347 --> 10:11.262
- [straining efforts]

10:11.306 --> 10:13.961
I can't close it!

10:14.004 --> 10:16.093
It won't close.

10:16.137 --> 10:20.054
It won't close!
It won't close.

10:20.097 --> 10:22.099
- You never were good
at packing light.

10:22.143 --> 10:25.799
- Oh, very funny.
I don't see you helping me.

10:27.409 --> 10:30.891
- You're the body
disposal expert.

10:30.934 --> 10:32.457
Dispose.

10:32.501 --> 10:38.463
- I am disposing as best
as I can!

10:38.507 --> 10:40.901
[panting]

10:44.905 --> 10:48.212
- Shoving a full-grown man
into a suitcase that size?

10:48.256 --> 10:49.474
- Shut up, Chucky.

10:49.518 --> 10:50.867
- It's amateur hour.

10:50.911 --> 10:52.390
- You're not helping.

10:52.434 --> 10:55.393
- The key is smaller pieces
for optimal packing.

10:55.437 --> 10:57.395
- Oh, so now you're
a packing genius.

10:57.439 --> 10:59.920
Smaller pieces.
Is that what you suggest?

10:59.963 --> 11:02.009
- It's like
rolling your t-shirts

11:02.052 --> 11:03.227
instead of folding 'em.

11:03.271 --> 11:05.273
- Shut up, Chucky!
- [laughs]

11:05.316 --> 11:07.318
- Get your leg off my suitcase!

11:09.451 --> 11:13.020
You want smaller pieces?
you can cut 'em yourself.

11:13.063 --> 11:15.979
[eerie music]

11:16.023 --> 11:18.765
♪

11:18.808 --> 11:21.158
- Uh!
[grunts]

11:21.202 --> 11:23.204
Oh, fuck!

11:25.554 --> 11:27.817
Uh! [inhales]

11:29.166 --> 11:31.691
Oh, no.
[whimpers]

11:35.346 --> 11:39.307
- 1960 Pontiac Parisian
four-door wide-track.

11:40.612 --> 11:41.962
Back when bigger
was unapologetically better.

11:42.005 --> 11:43.746
Comfortably seats six.

11:43.790 --> 11:46.923
perfect for the growing family,
by the way.

11:46.967 --> 11:50.666
389 V8 engine topped
with Tri-Power carburetor,

11:50.710 --> 11:53.756
making it the ultimate cruiser
of its day.

11:53.800 --> 11:55.932
Superior handling
and just the quietest purr

11:55.976 --> 11:57.673
from this pussycat.

11:57.717 --> 11:58.935
- And I love the color.

11:58.979 --> 12:00.763
- Coronado red.

12:00.807 --> 12:02.765
Just put on a fresh coat
last month.

12:02.809 --> 12:05.550
- Chucky, it's perfect.

12:05.594 --> 12:07.552
- You heard the lady.
How much?

12:07.596 --> 12:09.641
- 1,000 bucks.

12:09.685 --> 12:12.470
- Check okay?
- Fine.

12:12.514 --> 12:15.473
Oh, though there is
one thing that legally

12:15.517 --> 12:16.779
I am bound to disclose to you.

12:16.823 --> 12:18.781
- What's that?

12:18.825 --> 12:22.872
- Um, unfortunately, this car
was--there was an accident.

12:22.916 --> 12:25.788
- What happened?
- Young couple got killed.

12:25.832 --> 12:27.659
- How exactly?

12:27.703 --> 12:28.965
- Well, if you must know,

12:29.009 --> 12:30.488
I believe they
were decapitated.

12:30.532 --> 12:31.838
- Ooh.

12:33.927 --> 12:35.058
- Both of them?

12:35.102 --> 12:36.016
- More or less.

12:39.541 --> 12:40.977
- We'll take it.

12:41.021 --> 12:45.808
- Really? Great! Good for you!
[laughs]

12:45.852 --> 12:47.810
It's a stunning automobile,

12:47.854 --> 12:49.856
and a true classic
never goes out of style.

12:51.945 --> 12:53.990
- What'd you say?

12:54.034 --> 12:55.818
- I said you got
a real classic here.

12:55.862 --> 12:58.647
- Liar.

12:58.690 --> 13:00.518
- Pardon?
- Technically,

13:00.562 --> 13:03.086
it isn't even an antique.

13:03.130 --> 13:06.002
- [chuckles] Well, sure it is.

13:06.046 --> 13:09.136
It's vintage, retro.

13:09.179 --> 13:13.444
- It's not vintage
or retro

13:13.488 --> 13:15.142
or an antique.

13:15.185 --> 13:16.578
it's just old.

13:18.885 --> 13:19.799
Kinda like you.

13:22.453 --> 13:23.890
But don't worry,

13:23.933 --> 13:26.544
we're gonna give you
another paint job, too.

13:26.588 --> 13:29.852
[laughs]

13:29.896 --> 13:31.898
♪

13:31.941 --> 13:35.075
- [gurgling]

13:35.118 --> 13:36.728
Here you go.

13:36.772 --> 13:39.644
- That's 1,000 bucks.
- [laughs] That's cute.

13:42.604 --> 13:43.953
- Ahh.

13:47.043 --> 13:48.828
I just love that color.

13:48.871 --> 13:50.655
- Yeah, it matches
your lip gloss.

13:53.180 --> 13:56.052
[starts engine]

13:56.096 --> 13:57.880
- What's that?

13:57.924 --> 13:59.099
- It's a hobby.

13:59.142 --> 14:06.019
♪

14:20.120 --> 14:23.688
- [crying]

14:23.732 --> 14:26.648
[somber music]

14:26.691 --> 14:33.611
♪

14:35.962 --> 14:38.138
- I'm gonna call him in.

14:39.966 --> 14:42.577
Are you ready?

14:42.620 --> 14:44.535
- I don't know how anybody
could be ready for this.

14:45.667 --> 14:46.973
- I know.

14:57.331 --> 14:59.681
Junior.

14:59.724 --> 15:01.770
Can you come in here
for a minute, please?

15:09.647 --> 15:11.693
Hi.
Come have a seat for a sec.

15:20.093 --> 15:21.224
- Mom, what's going on?

15:24.924 --> 15:26.621
- Um--

15:28.884 --> 15:32.583
Your mother is--

15:32.627 --> 15:35.151
Your mother--

15:35.195 --> 15:36.805
Excuse me.

15:46.902 --> 15:48.643
- I'm sorry, sweetheart.

15:50.688 --> 15:53.996
Um, there's something
I have to tell you.

15:55.302 --> 15:57.217
And there's no easy way
to say it.

16:00.002 --> 16:01.221
I'm sick.

16:03.788 --> 16:05.877
- Sick?
- Hey.

16:05.921 --> 16:07.140
I don't want you to worry.

16:10.012 --> 16:13.711
- Mom?

16:13.755 --> 16:16.149
What's going on?

16:16.192 --> 16:23.069
♪

16:24.940 --> 16:28.813
- It's, um--

16:28.857 --> 16:30.337
It's cancer.

16:37.083 --> 16:40.042
- You're--you're gonna be okay,
right?

16:40.086 --> 16:42.305
You're gonna be okay?

16:42.349 --> 16:44.220
- We're gonna get through
this together, Junior.

16:46.048 --> 16:47.441
Please don't worry.

16:51.271 --> 16:54.056
Come here, buddy.

16:54.100 --> 16:55.753
Come here.

16:55.797 --> 16:57.146
Oh.

17:01.063 --> 17:03.109
I love you, buddy.

17:07.417 --> 17:09.115
Oh, my boy.

17:10.377 --> 17:12.988
- You ready? Look. Huh?

17:15.295 --> 17:18.298
I guess today
is my lucky day, huh?

17:18.341 --> 17:20.082
[laughs]

17:20.126 --> 17:21.953
- Funny.

17:21.997 --> 17:24.217
I don't remember you
being dumb enough

17:24.260 --> 17:26.132
to chase an inside straight,

17:26.175 --> 17:28.743
even if you are lucky enough
to get it.

17:28.786 --> 17:30.092
- [laughs]

17:30.136 --> 17:31.876
- Another beer?

17:31.920 --> 17:33.269
- No, I'm okay.

17:33.313 --> 17:35.010
- Ah, cuttin' back,
are you, Chucky?

17:40.320 --> 17:44.367
You know what this motel
reminds me of?

17:44.411 --> 17:49.111
It reminds me
of that night in Niagara.

17:49.155 --> 17:53.115
All those fond memories.
- [laughs]

17:53.159 --> 17:56.118
- It's why I chose this dump.

17:56.162 --> 17:58.903
Tell me, do you
remember Niagara, Chucky?

18:01.036 --> 18:03.125
- You know, I'm more of
a live-in-the-present

18:03.169 --> 18:04.431
kinda guy, huh?

18:04.474 --> 18:06.172
- Humor me.

18:06.215 --> 18:08.304
What was your favorite part?

18:12.134 --> 18:13.440
- Come on, Tiff.

18:13.483 --> 18:15.050
That was a long time ago.

18:15.094 --> 18:16.356
Raise you 100.

18:16.399 --> 18:18.793
- I call.

18:18.836 --> 18:23.014
Too long to remember
your own honeymoon, Chucky?

18:23.058 --> 18:24.364
Come on.

18:26.888 --> 18:31.327
- You know, my favorite part
was just being with you.

18:32.937 --> 18:36.245
- Aww, shucks.

18:36.289 --> 18:38.943
- [laughs]
- I never figured you to be

18:38.987 --> 18:42.164
the sentimental type, Chucky.

18:42.208 --> 18:44.123
- I'm all-in.

18:44.166 --> 18:46.429
- All right. I'm all-in too.

18:54.307 --> 18:55.482
[chuckles]

18:57.440 --> 18:59.094
Hello, Nica.

19:02.576 --> 19:05.840
Long time no see.

19:07.929 --> 19:10.366
- Nica? I'm not Nica.

19:10.410 --> 19:11.411
Why do you think I'm Nica?
I'm not--

19:11.454 --> 19:13.282
I'm not--

19:13.326 --> 19:16.285
[tense music]

19:16.329 --> 19:23.205
♪

19:23.249 --> 19:25.207
Is it Chucky doesn't bluff?

19:25.251 --> 19:28.210
- Ohh, Chucky bluffs.

19:28.254 --> 19:31.561
But he doesn't chew
on his fingernails.

19:31.605 --> 19:34.303
[laughs]

19:34.347 --> 19:38.525
Besides, I stabbed you
in the thigh ten minutes ago.

19:38.568 --> 19:41.223
You didn't feel a thing.

19:41.267 --> 19:42.964
Ooh, if it'd have been Chucky,

19:43.007 --> 19:45.401
he woulda screamed
like a banshee.

19:45.445 --> 19:48.796
But not you,
being paralyzed and all.

19:53.235 --> 19:54.976
- What are you gonna do to me?

19:55.019 --> 19:57.544
- I don't know.
that's an interesting question.

19:57.587 --> 20:00.938
You see, the thing is, Nica,

20:00.982 --> 20:04.246
I spent some with you,
I spent some time with Chucky,

20:04.290 --> 20:06.161
and I gotta say,

20:06.205 --> 20:07.815
I like you better.

20:08.598 --> 20:10.252
- [chuckles]

20:10.296 --> 20:11.993
You do?

20:12.036 --> 20:14.213
- Do you wanna know a secret?

20:16.345 --> 20:17.564
- Sure.

20:20.088 --> 20:24.135
- Sometimes,
when we're together, I--

20:24.179 --> 20:27.530
I see you looking at me,

20:27.574 --> 20:30.098
and I know it's you.

20:30.141 --> 20:35.277
It's not Chucky,
it's you, and...

20:35.321 --> 20:37.105
I live for those moments.

20:39.020 --> 20:42.284
I want to have those moments
all the time.

20:42.328 --> 20:45.853
- Mm-hmm.
- I--[sighs]

20:48.377 --> 20:50.161
Guess what?

20:50.205 --> 20:53.034
I have a surprise
for you, Nica.

20:53.077 --> 20:55.341
I bought us a house

20:55.384 --> 20:58.996
right here in Hackensack.

20:59.040 --> 21:03.174
You know, they say the saints
look over everybody

21:03.218 --> 21:05.307
that lives in Hackensack,

21:05.351 --> 21:11.139
even non-traditional couples
like ourselves.

21:11.182 --> 21:16.362
The only problem is...

21:16.405 --> 21:19.060
How do I keep you
in the driver's seat

21:19.103 --> 21:21.976
instead of that rat Chucky?
- [laughs]

21:25.414 --> 21:28.156
[humming]

21:28.199 --> 21:29.636
Ahh!

21:36.991 --> 21:38.514
- He's not on Insta.

21:39.123 --> 21:40.690
- Not on Snap.

21:40.734 --> 21:43.519
- Not on Twitter.

21:43.563 --> 21:46.914
- Well...
- What?

21:46.957 --> 21:48.437
- I Googled Andy Barclay and
got an article

21:48.481 --> 21:50.047
from two weeks ago.

21:50.091 --> 21:53.616
"Violent Patient Escapes
Harrogate Psychiatric Hospital

21:53.660 --> 21:55.009
Manhunt Underway"

21:55.923 --> 21:58.839
- [sighs] Great sign.

21:58.882 --> 22:00.231
[doorbell dings]

22:00.275 --> 22:02.712
Be right back.

22:02.756 --> 22:05.498
- Wait, Harrogate,
where is that?

22:05.541 --> 22:08.892
- Rhode Island.
- Rhode Island?

22:08.936 --> 22:12.243
Wait, I got a call from Rhode
Island about a month ago.

22:12.287 --> 22:13.941
Holy shit,
that must be Andy Barclay.

22:18.249 --> 22:20.251
- God.

22:20.295 --> 22:25.213
Junior, I'm so sorry.

22:25.256 --> 22:27.737
- I just feel like everything's
falling apart right now,

22:27.781 --> 22:29.043
you know?

22:29.086 --> 22:33.874
My mom, my uncle.

22:33.917 --> 22:35.049
Even you and me.

22:37.138 --> 22:41.098
- No. No, not us.

22:41.142 --> 22:42.665
I'm always here for you.

22:42.709 --> 22:46.060
- Hey, Lexy, he's on Facebook!

22:46.103 --> 22:48.454
- I just feel like you're
somewhere else these days.

22:50.804 --> 22:53.154
- I'm sorry, what?

22:53.197 --> 22:54.590
- You see what I mean?

22:54.634 --> 22:56.287
The fuck, Lex?

22:56.331 --> 22:57.985
It's like I don't even
exist to you anymore!

22:59.160 --> 23:03.686
- No. No, that's--
that's not true.

23:03.730 --> 23:06.167
I'm always here for you.

23:06.210 --> 23:08.561
I love you.

23:08.604 --> 23:10.737
And it's like you said,
everything has just been

23:10.780 --> 23:12.739
such a mess lately,
and I just want to protect you.

23:12.782 --> 23:15.611
- No.

23:15.655 --> 23:17.134
- No?

23:17.178 --> 23:19.702
- It's over.

23:19.746 --> 23:25.752
We're done.

23:25.795 --> 23:28.015
- No.

23:28.058 --> 23:30.017
No, Junior, please.

23:30.060 --> 23:31.932
Please don't do this.
We can fix this.

23:31.975 --> 23:33.934
- I just did.

23:37.241 --> 23:40.680
[door opens, shuts]

23:43.073 --> 23:45.336
- Wait, how old's
this guy again?

23:45.380 --> 23:47.643
- Um, 40.

23:47.687 --> 23:50.820
- God help us.

23:50.864 --> 23:52.779
- Hi. This is Andy Barclay.
Leave a message.

23:52.822 --> 23:53.823
[beep]

23:53.867 --> 23:56.304
- Shit.

23:56.347 --> 23:58.959
[phone ringing]

23:59.002 --> 24:00.134
- Uh--

24:02.092 --> 24:03.659
- Andy Barclay?

24:03.703 --> 24:04.834
- Jake Wheeler.

24:04.878 --> 24:06.880
Where are you?

24:06.923 --> 24:09.622
- In a kitchen in Hackensack.

24:09.665 --> 24:11.841
- Hackensack. Figures.

24:11.885 --> 24:14.670
- You know about Chucky,
and you're still alive.

24:14.714 --> 24:16.716
Makes you one of the lucky few.

24:16.759 --> 24:19.022
It's a shitty club to be in,
but welcome.

24:19.066 --> 24:20.850
- At first I thought
I was going crazy.

24:20.894 --> 24:22.112
- Well, you haven't told
anyone, have you?

24:22.156 --> 24:23.636
- No. No one.

24:23.679 --> 24:25.638
- Look, you feel like
you're going crazy?

24:25.681 --> 24:28.771
That's exactly what everyone
will think if you tell them.

24:28.815 --> 24:31.731
Speaking of crazy, Chucky's
not with anyone, is he?

24:31.774 --> 24:33.689
A woman? Two women?

24:33.733 --> 24:34.908
- Uh--

24:34.951 --> 24:37.171
No, I don't think so, but

24:37.214 --> 24:39.739
listen, Andy, I have, like,
a million questions.

24:39.782 --> 24:42.089
We're out of time,
and we need your help.

24:42.132 --> 24:43.394
How do we find him?

24:43.438 --> 24:45.701
- Oh, you don't have
to find Chucky.

24:45.745 --> 24:47.137
He'll find you.

24:47.181 --> 24:48.878
And if he can't find you,

24:48.922 --> 24:51.620
he'll go after your
whole family to get to you.

24:51.664 --> 24:53.927
- He killed
our foster parents, Jake.

24:53.970 --> 24:55.755
He'll stop at nothing.

24:57.757 --> 25:00.716
- Oh, and Jake, it'll be
somewhere he's familiar with,

25:00.760 --> 25:02.326
and you're
at your most vulnerable.

25:02.370 --> 25:05.068
That's exactly
where he'll find you.

25:05.112 --> 25:06.200
- Junior's house.

25:07.375 --> 25:09.769
- Not a bad place
to spring a trap.

25:09.812 --> 25:11.031
- Well, text me the address.

25:11.074 --> 25:12.772
We're on our way.

25:12.815 --> 25:17.733
♪

25:20.823 --> 25:22.912
- [laughs]

25:22.956 --> 25:24.958
[humming]

25:27.482 --> 25:31.921
Gladys! Big day!

25:31.965 --> 25:35.925
- Congratulations, Miss Tilly.
- Thank you. Thank you.

25:35.969 --> 25:37.884
- Well, you know, the house
has beautiful bones.

25:37.927 --> 25:40.451
- Mm-hmm.
- It just needs a little TLC.

25:40.495 --> 25:42.802
- Mm-hmm.
- And someone like yourself...

25:42.845 --> 25:44.934
- Yes.
- With a vision to restore it

25:44.978 --> 25:47.154
to its mid-century glory.

25:47.197 --> 25:51.288
- Yes. We have big plans
for this place.

25:51.332 --> 25:53.160
- We?
- Yes.

25:53.203 --> 25:56.250
Me and my fiancée
will be moving in immediately.

25:56.293 --> 25:59.775
- Oh, congratulations!
That's wonderful!

25:59.819 --> 26:00.863
- Thank you. Yes.

26:00.907 --> 26:02.386
- What brings you
to Hackensack?

26:02.430 --> 26:05.215
- Well, my fiancée
grew up here, actually.

26:05.259 --> 26:07.130
Right in this very house.

26:07.174 --> 26:09.002
- Oh!
- Mm-hmm.

26:09.045 --> 26:14.224
- I--it's just been empty
ever since--

26:14.268 --> 26:18.054
- Ever since the murders.
Yes.

26:18.098 --> 26:20.491
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

26:20.535 --> 26:23.973
- Oh, so it was
your fiancée's parents that--

26:24.017 --> 26:27.237
- [laughs] Yes. Yes.

26:27.281 --> 26:29.500
So many memories.

26:29.544 --> 26:33.809
- Okay. You know,
I almost forgot.

26:33.853 --> 26:35.376
You've already started
getting some mail.

26:35.419 --> 26:37.857
- Oh! [gasps]

26:37.900 --> 26:40.294
Oh!

26:40.337 --> 26:41.730
- There you go.

26:41.774 --> 26:43.906
- I have an online
shopping addiction.

26:43.950 --> 26:47.344
- Okay. Well, you have
a good night, Miss Tilly.

26:47.388 --> 26:49.738
- Oh, would you
like my autograph?

26:49.782 --> 26:51.174
- Next time!

26:51.218 --> 26:53.133
- Okay.

26:53.176 --> 26:56.092
Weirdo.

26:56.136 --> 26:58.399
[humming]

27:00.401 --> 27:04.535
I'll put you
right here for now.

27:04.579 --> 27:06.407
And...

27:06.450 --> 27:11.847
♪

27:11.891 --> 27:14.502
- [whimpering softly]

27:14.545 --> 27:17.461
- Welcome home!

27:17.505 --> 27:19.028
[sighs]

27:21.814 --> 27:24.294
- [grunting]

27:24.338 --> 27:28.124
- Hold still!
Hold still! Hold still!

27:28.168 --> 27:30.387
It's for your own good.

27:30.431 --> 27:32.433
There, that's better.

27:32.476 --> 27:34.304
That didn't hurt, did it?

27:34.348 --> 27:38.874
You're such a baby.
[laughs]

27:38.918 --> 27:41.355
Look how sweet you look.

27:41.398 --> 27:44.924
Oh, oh. Ohh.

27:46.273 --> 27:48.231
Goodbye, sweet face.

27:48.275 --> 27:51.060
Don't wait up.
[laughs]

27:56.022 --> 27:58.111
Don't do anything
I wouldn't do.

27:58.154 --> 28:00.243
- [grunting]
[door shuts]

28:02.028 --> 28:08.077
[muffled]
Help! Help!

28:08.121 --> 28:10.036
[screams]

28:19.872 --> 28:21.830
- I want my lawyer.

28:21.874 --> 28:23.440
- Someone's on their way.

28:23.484 --> 28:25.355
Besides, I don't
need you to talk.

28:25.399 --> 28:29.098
Just listen.

28:29.142 --> 28:31.100
Here's what we got.

28:31.144 --> 28:34.582
You were the last person
to see Principal McVey alive.

28:34.625 --> 28:37.150
You were next in line
for her job.

28:37.193 --> 28:40.066
We found your fingerprints
everywhere in the office

28:40.109 --> 28:43.330
and the crime scene and...this.

28:44.897 --> 28:47.203
- Of course my fingerprints
are everywhere.

28:47.247 --> 28:48.857
I work at the school.

28:48.901 --> 28:52.426
- I haven't even gotten started
on Oliver Hayden.

28:52.469 --> 28:55.081
He was your student, wasn't he?

28:55.124 --> 28:58.475
Oh, and then there's
your juvenile record.

28:58.519 --> 29:01.565
Maybe McVey found out
about your delinquent past?

29:04.351 --> 29:07.484
So, yeah, wait for the lawyer.

29:10.966 --> 29:12.359
You're gonna need one.

29:16.711 --> 29:19.148
- Rachel Fairchild,
a biology teacher

29:19.192 --> 29:21.324
at Perry Middle School,
has been charged

29:21.368 --> 29:25.459
with three counts of homicide
by Hackensack police.

29:25.502 --> 29:27.635
The recent murders are part
of an alarming trend

29:27.678 --> 29:29.985
in local violence,
which have threatened

29:30.029 --> 29:32.553
reelection prospects
for Mayor Michelle Cross.

29:36.731 --> 29:37.863
- Do you want me to leave you
the keys

29:37.906 --> 29:38.951
in case you want
to listen to the radio?

29:40.735 --> 29:43.216
Okay, I'll leave them
just in case.

29:46.132 --> 29:47.873
- Mom?
- Mm-hmm?

29:51.006 --> 29:52.616
- What do you talk
about in there?

29:53.574 --> 29:55.402
- [sighs]

30:02.496 --> 30:04.933
All the things we don't
talk about at home.

30:07.588 --> 30:09.068
- Why don't we talk
about them at home?

30:12.114 --> 30:13.420
- I don't know.

30:18.468 --> 30:20.340
- You talk about me?

30:21.254 --> 30:23.647
- All the time.

30:23.691 --> 30:27.260
You know, your my favorite
topic of conversation?

30:32.352 --> 30:34.049
Come here, buddy.

30:38.967 --> 30:41.013
I love you.

30:41.056 --> 30:42.449
- I love you, too.

30:45.147 --> 30:47.758
- I'll be right back, okay?

30:47.802 --> 30:54.200
♪

30:54.243 --> 30:55.679
[laughter]

31:05.646 --> 31:08.388
- I told them.

31:08.431 --> 31:09.650
I was honest.

31:12.131 --> 31:15.699
About the cancer,
and my chances.

31:15.743 --> 31:17.788
It's all out in the open now.

31:17.832 --> 31:20.182
- That's good.

31:20.226 --> 31:23.751
I imagine it was unburdening

31:23.794 --> 31:27.276
to share your truth
with people close to you.

31:27.320 --> 31:29.452
- No.

31:29.496 --> 31:31.150
It was horrible.

31:33.456 --> 31:36.111
- I didn't need to share my
pain,

31:36.155 --> 31:37.721
or my fear, or my worry.

31:39.506 --> 31:42.683
Some things aren't meant
to be shared.

31:42.726 --> 31:47.296
So, I've made another decision.

31:47.340 --> 31:50.038
I'm refusing treatment.

31:50.082 --> 31:52.171
- Bree, we've talked
about depression before.

31:52.214 --> 31:54.695
It's very common for people
with your diagnosis

31:54.738 --> 31:56.305
to feel hopeless.

31:56.349 --> 32:00.614
- Dr. Mixter, I don't feel
depressed or hopeless.

32:00.657 --> 32:03.399
Literally,
for the first time in weeks.

32:05.706 --> 32:08.491
I just wanna live my life
with my family,

32:08.535 --> 32:10.754
with whatever time
that I have left.

32:10.798 --> 32:13.801
Because every day is a gift.

32:13.844 --> 32:15.803
For all of us.

32:15.846 --> 32:17.326
- That's true.

32:17.370 --> 32:18.762
- I could walk out
of this office right now

32:18.806 --> 32:19.850
and get hit by a bus.

32:19.894 --> 32:21.678
Who knows what could happen?

32:21.722 --> 32:24.855
- Could be something
very special.

32:24.899 --> 32:27.380
- The important thing is for me
to savor what time I have left,

32:29.208 --> 32:31.253
and welcome whatever's waiting
around that corner

32:31.297 --> 32:33.081
with open arms.

32:33.125 --> 32:36.693
- ♪ I've been having dreams

32:36.737 --> 32:40.523
♪ Splashin' in
the summer stream ♪

32:40.567 --> 32:44.266
♪ Trip and I fall in

32:44.310 --> 32:48.096
♪ I want it to happen

32:48.140 --> 32:52.100
♪ My body turns to ice

32:52.144 --> 32:55.712
♪ Crushin' weight
of paradise ♪

32:55.756 --> 32:59.542
♪ Solid block of gold
lying in the cold ♪

32:59.586 --> 33:05.157
♪ I feel right at home

33:05.200 --> 33:08.812
♪ Wait if I'm on fire

33:08.856 --> 33:12.729
♪ How am I so deep in love?

33:12.773 --> 33:17.212
♪ When I dream of dying

33:17.256 --> 33:21.173
♪ I never feel so loved

33:22.913 --> 33:24.654
- [laughs]

33:24.698 --> 33:28.658
♪

33:28.702 --> 33:31.661
- ♪ I never feel so loved

33:31.705 --> 33:38.538
♪

33:38.581 --> 33:39.800
- [laughs]

33:41.932 --> 33:43.673
[grunts]

33:43.717 --> 33:45.110
- [screams]

33:46.198 --> 33:53.118
♪

33:54.554 --> 33:56.773
- ♪ Wait if I'm on fire

33:56.817 --> 33:58.601
- [kisses]

33:58.645 --> 34:01.691
- ♪ How am I so deep
in love? ♪

34:01.735 --> 34:04.564
♪ When I dream of dying

34:06.348 --> 34:08.307
- Ah!
[crashing]

34:08.350 --> 34:10.178
[gasping]

34:10.222 --> 34:13.442
Mom?
[panting]

34:13.486 --> 34:16.967
- ♪ How am I so deep
in love? ♪

34:17.011 --> 34:18.752
♪ When I dream of fire

34:18.795 --> 34:21.450
- Ahh!

34:21.494 --> 34:27.282
Mom--Mom!

34:27.326 --> 34:28.979
[screams]

34:31.591 --> 34:34.463
[dark music]

34:34.942 --> 34:40.861
♪

34:40.904 --> 34:42.689
- I know it's a lot
to process right now.

34:45.170 --> 34:48.825
- She didn't seem--

34:48.869 --> 34:51.785
I don't understand.

34:51.828 --> 34:55.005
She made it sound
like everything was fine.

34:55.049 --> 34:57.617
That she had it under control.

34:57.660 --> 35:01.011
She didn't say anything to you?

35:01.055 --> 35:03.492
You're her fuckin' therapist.
You didn't see any signs?

35:05.190 --> 35:08.671
- It's normal to feel angry
at times like this.

35:08.715 --> 35:10.151
When faced with
their own mortality,

35:10.195 --> 35:13.633
some patients try
to regain control

35:13.676 --> 35:15.591
the only way they can.

35:18.028 --> 35:22.076
- So, that's it.

35:22.120 --> 35:24.122
She just decided
to hell with all of us.

35:27.690 --> 35:28.865
She just gave up.

35:28.909 --> 35:31.999
- Her cancer had metastasized.

35:32.042 --> 35:35.611
Her prognosis,
even with chemo, was grim.

35:35.655 --> 35:40.268
She didn't want her treatment
to overtake your lives.

35:40.312 --> 35:44.098
You must understand your
mother loved you all very much.

35:47.667 --> 35:49.147
- Thank you for coming by.

35:53.107 --> 35:55.936
- If you ever need to talk,
don't hesitate to call.

36:04.988 --> 36:07.165
I'm so very sorry
for your loss.

36:07.208 --> 36:08.905
Take care of yourselves.

36:08.949 --> 36:13.171
- Junior, I don't think
your mother killed herself.

36:13.214 --> 36:19.307
♪

36:19.351 --> 36:22.354
- Stay the fuck away from me.

36:22.397 --> 36:24.660
We were fine
before you came along.

36:27.228 --> 36:30.144
["Cape Fear" theme playing]

36:30.188 --> 36:37.107
♪

36:43.331 --> 36:44.898
[knock at door]

36:44.941 --> 36:48.380
- Hey. I have to head back
to the station.

36:48.423 --> 36:50.295
I have a busy night
ahead of me.

36:50.338 --> 36:52.906
If you're hungry,
I left some soup in the fridge.

36:52.949 --> 36:55.865
- Thanks.

36:55.909 --> 36:57.302
- Curfew is still in effect.

36:57.345 --> 36:58.955
Promise me you'll stay inside.

37:04.787 --> 37:11.141
Devon, I know I've been
hard on you lately, and...

37:11.185 --> 37:13.709
I know that
I was wrong about Jake.

37:13.753 --> 37:15.407
And I'm sorry.

37:15.450 --> 37:17.191
I should have trusted you.

37:21.239 --> 37:23.763
- Hey, Mom.

37:23.806 --> 37:25.243
Can I ask you something?

37:30.422 --> 37:31.901
- Shoot.

37:38.908 --> 37:40.867
- How do you know
if you really like someone?

37:42.999 --> 37:45.263
- When I first met your father,

37:45.306 --> 37:48.309
I couldn't stop
thinking about him.

37:48.353 --> 37:52.052
I had butterflies in my stomach
whenever he was around.

37:52.095 --> 37:54.707
[laughs]

37:54.750 --> 37:57.318
Is that how you feel?

37:57.362 --> 37:58.319
About Jake?

38:02.149 --> 38:06.066
- Yeah.

38:06.109 --> 38:10.288
You know, I was worried you
wouldn't look at me the same.

38:10.331 --> 38:13.682
- Honey, this doesn't
change anything.

38:14.988 --> 38:16.859
You're my son.

38:16.903 --> 38:19.993
And I'll always love you. Okay?

38:25.215 --> 38:27.435
- I love you, Mom.

38:27.479 --> 38:28.958
Thank you.

38:32.745 --> 38:34.355
- I miss your movie nights.

38:34.399 --> 38:36.401
Maybe next week
we could do a double feature.

38:36.444 --> 38:38.838
You could invite Jake.

38:38.881 --> 38:41.231
- Maybe.
- Okay.

38:54.897 --> 38:56.159
[rewinding video]

38:58.248 --> 39:05.168
♪

39:16.397 --> 39:18.791
- What is that?

39:18.834 --> 39:20.532
- Well, it's
a monofilament line.

39:20.575 --> 39:22.360
Got it from
Sam's Fishing Gear.

39:22.403 --> 39:23.970
See, what I do is I stretch it
across the windows

39:24.013 --> 39:27.060
and the doors, and attach it
to Andy's teddy bear here.

39:27.103 --> 39:28.888
If the bear moves 1/4 inch,

39:28.931 --> 39:30.193
I'll know if the Holy Ghost
is sneaking in.

39:32.065 --> 39:38.985
♪

39:41.466 --> 39:44.947
[beeping]

39:44.991 --> 39:46.906
[electricity crackling]

39:46.949 --> 39:49.909
[tense music]

39:49.952 --> 39:56.829
♪

40:08.841 --> 40:10.843
- We'll know if the Holy Ghost
sneaks in.

40:10.886 --> 40:11.931
- What?

40:11.974 --> 40:13.411
- She's our alarm.

40:13.454 --> 40:15.587
- They have an alarm,
and it's from this century.

40:15.630 --> 40:17.980
- Well, we don't
want the cops here.

40:18.024 --> 40:19.460
I don't want my mom here, okay?

40:24.073 --> 40:26.249
- Where's Junior
and your uncle?

40:26.293 --> 40:27.468
- Funeral home.

40:27.512 --> 40:28.904
- Why aren't you with them?

40:28.948 --> 40:30.297
- They need to be alone.

40:30.340 --> 40:32.299
And so do we.

40:32.342 --> 40:33.605
Best vantage point is upstairs.

40:33.648 --> 40:35.215
My room.

40:37.217 --> 40:39.349
- Rock-paper-scissors?

40:44.093 --> 40:45.878
- Seriously?

40:45.921 --> 40:47.488
[sighs] Jesus.

40:52.667 --> 40:55.191
- Just don't touch
any of my stuff, all right?

40:55.235 --> 40:58.151
[phone buzzing]

41:10.206 --> 41:12.078
[thunder rumbles]

41:14.036 --> 41:17.213
- Hey, I talked to my mom.

41:17.257 --> 41:18.563
Told her I'm into someone.

41:20.390 --> 41:22.044
- [chuckles]
- You.

41:23.959 --> 41:27.441
- Um, how--how'd she take it?

41:27.485 --> 41:30.444
- Now that she knows you're not
a psycho, she's cool.

41:32.533 --> 41:36.189
- Yeah. Well, maybe,

41:36.232 --> 41:38.408
you know,
when this is all over,

41:38.452 --> 41:40.541
maybe we could go on a date?

41:40.585 --> 41:44.110
You know, one that doesn't
involve hunting a killer doll.

41:44.153 --> 41:45.938
- Definitely.

41:45.981 --> 41:47.417
- Okay.

41:47.461 --> 41:49.245
- What kind of movies
are you into?

41:49.289 --> 41:52.553
- Um, horror movies.

41:52.597 --> 41:54.250
Well, I mean,
I used to, anyway.

41:56.601 --> 41:58.428
- Favorite final girl?

41:58.472 --> 42:00.256
- Laurie Strode, hands down.

42:00.300 --> 42:02.215
- Jamie Lee's gonna win
the Saturn this year.

42:02.258 --> 42:04.478
- Dude, she's gonna win
an Oscar. She's magnificent.

42:04.522 --> 42:06.524
- She's fabulous.

42:06.567 --> 42:08.134
Uh, anyway.

42:10.353 --> 42:13.052
I have a feeling
it's gonna take a lot more than

42:13.095 --> 42:15.707
"Goosebumps" and Pennywise
to scare us.

42:15.750 --> 42:17.578
[both gasp]

42:17.622 --> 42:21.713
♪

42:21.756 --> 42:23.671
- Chucky's here.

42:27.719 --> 42:30.591
[tense music]

42:31.070 --> 42:37.555
♪

42:57.923 --> 43:01.100
[crashing]
[Chucky laughs]

43:01.143 --> 43:08.020
♪

43:35.874 --> 43:38.877
- Oh, shit.

43:38.920 --> 43:40.661
That never happened
in "Cape Fear."

43:40.705 --> 43:42.054
- Of course not.

43:42.097 --> 43:44.230
De Niro could have
never fit down that chimney.

43:44.273 --> 43:46.580
- No, dude.
He was totally ripped in that.

43:49.191 --> 43:51.977
- Hey, make sure he
doesn't double back.

43:53.979 --> 44:00.899
♪

44:31.059 --> 44:37.979
♪

44:39.807 --> 44:42.680
[gas hissing]

44:49.121 --> 44:56.041
♪

45:14.407 --> 45:16.104
- Hey.

45:16.148 --> 45:19.194
Where is he?
- I don't know.

45:19.238 --> 45:20.979
He's--he's messing with us.

45:29.161 --> 45:34.644
♪

45:34.688 --> 45:38.387
- Jake?

45:38.431 --> 45:41.086
Jake!

45:41.129 --> 45:42.304
[screams]

45:42.348 --> 45:44.742
- I got you now, bitch!

45:47.353 --> 45:50.051
But I'll let you go
on one condition.

45:51.096 --> 45:53.751
- [panting]

45:53.794 --> 45:55.753
What?

45:57.929 --> 46:01.280
- All you gotta do
is kill Jake.

46:06.764 --> 46:08.896
Everybody's gotta die sometime,
so--

46:08.940 --> 46:10.115
- That's true.

46:10.158 --> 46:12.857
- I mean, I've died myself
many times,

46:12.900 --> 46:14.336
so it's no big deal.

46:18.079 --> 46:23.041
- You want me to kill Jake?
Why?

46:23.084 --> 46:26.261
- Don't tell me you've
never thought about it.

46:26.305 --> 46:28.786
You get off on hurting Jake.

46:33.094 --> 46:34.052
- Yeah.

46:37.142 --> 46:39.927
Okay, fine, I'll admit it.

46:39.971 --> 46:41.146
I have thought about it.

46:43.061 --> 46:45.803
You're right.

46:45.846 --> 46:48.196
I do wanna kill Jake.

46:48.240 --> 46:49.284
- I knew it.

46:50.895 --> 46:52.810
- You wanna know I'd do it?

46:52.853 --> 46:54.289
- Duh!

46:56.030 --> 46:58.163
I'm all ears.
[beeping]

46:58.206 --> 46:59.729
- Okay.

47:03.733 --> 47:05.170
I'd beat him to death...

47:07.999 --> 47:09.435
with this.

47:11.176 --> 47:12.786
- Can I watch?

47:12.830 --> 47:13.831
[floorboard creaks]

47:13.874 --> 47:16.007
Aha!

47:16.050 --> 47:18.792
Do it, Lexy!
Kill him!

47:18.836 --> 47:19.880
- Damn it!

47:19.924 --> 47:21.229
- Ha ha!
- Ahh!

47:21.273 --> 47:23.405
[Tazer crackling]
- No! [screams]

47:23.449 --> 47:24.406
- Jake!

47:24.450 --> 47:25.886
♪

47:25.930 --> 47:27.322
Shit!

47:27.366 --> 47:28.889
[beeping]
- Come on, come on, come on!

47:28.933 --> 47:30.499
♪

47:30.543 --> 47:33.328
- [groans]

47:33.372 --> 47:35.940
I'm too old for this shit.

47:43.425 --> 47:46.385
[laughs]

47:48.866 --> 47:50.258
[beeping]

47:50.302 --> 47:52.782
- Guys.
He's headed back downstairs.

47:52.826 --> 47:53.871
- Okay.
[grunting]

47:56.177 --> 47:57.831
- He didn't even try
to kill me.

47:57.875 --> 47:59.180
- Me neither.
- What the hell?

47:59.224 --> 48:02.880
- Hello?
[police radio chatter]

48:02.923 --> 48:04.969
Devon, are you here?

48:05.012 --> 48:06.535
- Mom?

48:06.579 --> 48:08.015
- Ahh!

48:08.059 --> 48:10.191
Hey, Devon, watch this!

48:10.235 --> 48:11.540
- [screams]

48:11.584 --> 48:13.412
- Mom! Mom!

48:13.455 --> 48:15.196
- [screaming]

48:15.240 --> 48:17.372
- Whoa! [laughs]
Ahh!

48:18.286 --> 48:19.984
[screaming]

48:20.027 --> 48:21.507
- Mom!

48:23.291 --> 48:25.380
[bones cracking]

48:25.424 --> 48:30.037
[Chucky laughs]

48:30.081 --> 48:36.957
♪

48:43.224 --> 48:50.144
♪

48:59.110 --> 49:06.030
♪
